<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<Data CreatedBy="admin" CreatedOn="634096314931620068" UpdatedBy="admin" UpdatedOn="634096333907975072">
  <Properties />
  <Nodes>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement1"><![CDATA[<p><strong>Essential manual for concepts and features</strong></p><p>CompaninonKit provides extensive demonstrational help for Visual&nbsp;WebGui concepts and includes examples for available controls.</p><p><strong>Provides ready-to-run examples</strong></p><p>The examples demonstrate appearance, behavior and features.<br />They are well organized, searchable and ready for download and browsing.<br />The examples ready to be included in your projects for further usage and customization.<br />They were built considering best practices of Visual WebGui platform.</p><p><strong>Live demo with step by step instructions</strong><br /><br />CompanionKit is a live application and provides a way to get familiar with features and concepts.<br />The examples are interactive and have step by step instructions to control exposed functionality.</p><p><strong>Demonstration of complex Web application</strong><br /><br />CompanionKit is an expandable application with multiple examples.<br />It was built with extensive usage of Visual WebGui&nbsp;platform.<br />CompanionKit itself could be used to learn how to build a complex Web application.</p><p><strong>Freely distributed and open source</strong></p><p>It was inroduced with version 6.4, freely distributed and open source.<br />It's well documented and includes best practices for implementation of common tasks.</p><p><strong>C# and VB.NET examples</strong></p><p>Both C# and VB.NET examples are included to demonstrate the functionality for available controls and concepts of Visual WebGUI platform.</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Code="ParagraphElement2"><![CDATA[<p><strong>How to start ?</strong></p><p>First of all you have to see <a target="_blank" href="http://visualwebgui.com/tabid/320/articleType/ArticleView/articleId/804/Intro-to-new-Developer-CompanionKit.aspx">video tutorial</a> prepared to introduce features and functionality of CompanionKit. The tutorial demonstrates all required to operate the CompanionKit. You will learn how to search required functionality, browse and download the code and&nbsp;include a code snippet to&nbsp;a stand alone&nbsp;application as a starting point.</p><p>The CompaionKit application is installed with <strong>Visual WebGui SDK </strong>and could be downloaded <a target="_blank" href="http://visualwebgui.com/tabid/110/default.aspx">here</a>. <br />You&nbsp;can&nbsp;browse code snippets online or install and run them locally.<br />&nbsp;</p>]]></Paragraph>
    <Image Code="ImageElement1" Resource="companionkit.banner.PNG" Type="Resource" />
  </Nodes>
</Data>